02/06/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- Police arrested a former justice minister and six other people Tuesday (June 1st) as part of ongoing investigations into the activities of the so-called Ergenekon organisation, suspected of plotting to topple the government. 
Seyfi Oktay, who served as justice minister in several coalition governments in the early 1990s, was detained after police raided several properties he owns in Ankara. 
Other arrests occurred in Antalya and Istanbul. 
(Vatan, Zaman - 02/06/10; Anadolu news agency, Reuters, Hurriyet - 01/06/10)
